narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: A comprehensive overview of beginner L1-L2 French from a true starting point of no knowledge. I build a solid foundation of vocabulary, grammar, and knowledge of francophone culture, and also developed all aspects of language learning, including auditory, writing, speaking, and reading.
The course covered basic French grammar and vocabulary and goes through two semesters worth of textbook chapters in one.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths: you receive a super in-depth introduction to the French language and culture and truly learn A LOT, clear schedule with assignments and expectations, class gets close through lots of interaction, Madame Sherak -- she wants everyone to succeed and genuinely cares about the course and her students

Weaknesses: Because the course moves so quickly, some topics seemed a bit rushed and left a lot of practice and reading to be done at home

This class was well-organized and went through all the material for each chapter systematically without rushing through anything. The class environment was also very positive and the Prof. Sherak is very welcoming and inclusive. The class did require a large time commitment, but I think that it was altogether reasonable for 2 credits and the assignments are very consistent in terms of workload for each class, so it's easy to plan for.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would absolutely recommend this course to a student if they want to learn a new language quickly and have the time and level of commitment that the course requires. The course is a lot of work, but the reward is huge. I'd highly recommend this opportunity to anyone on the fence!

I would recommend this course for a student that has enough space in their schedule to dedicate two credits worth of work to the course and would like to learn French quickly. I found it to be a nice class for starting another language late into my undergraduate studies.
